<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1765,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1873,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[322,651,1873,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref14337" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (1999) Brachyceran Diptera in Cretaceous ambers and Mesozoic diversification of the Eremoneura. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 239, 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="1999">Grimaldi &amp; Cumming (1999)</bibRefCitation>
established this genus to include a single species found in amber from Bcharre, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[357,455,1909,1935]" name="Lebanon" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(Lower Cretaceous, Barremian): 
<taxonomicName authority="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming. Nel et al. (2017)" authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming. Nel" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis box="[834,1059,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Avenaphora hispida</emphasis>
Grimaldi &amp; Cumming. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, A. &amp; Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C." pageId="1" pageNumber="412" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref15625" refString="Nel, A., Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C. (2017) Two new long-legged flies in the Santonian amber of France (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Cretaceous Research, 69, 1 - 5. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2016.08.009" type="journal article" year="2017">
Nel 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described a second species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[566,701,1945,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[566,701,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from amber of Piolenc, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1150,1946,1972]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">France</collectingCountry>
(Upper Cretaceous, early Santonian): 
<taxonomicName authority="Nel, Garrouste &amp; Daugeron. Grimaldi &amp; Cumming (1999)" authorityName="Nel, Garrouste &amp; Daugeron. Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[290,1084,1981,2008]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallica">
<emphasis box="[290,307,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[323,401,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">gallica</emphasis>
Nel, Garrouste &amp; Daugeron. 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[746,1084,1981,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref14337" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (1999) Brachyceran Diptera in Cretaceous ambers and Mesozoic diversification of the Eremoneura. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 239, 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="1999">Grimaldi &amp; Cumming (1999)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have listed plesiomorphic and apomorphic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[418,553,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,553,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter includes the dichoptic condition of the male, loss of cell dm (dm-m absent), and the form of the hypopygium, which is relatively symmetrical externally. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, A. &amp; Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C." box="[1097,1279,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref15625" refString="Nel, A., Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C. (2017) Two new long-legged flies in the Santonian amber of France (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Cretaceous Research, 69, 1 - 5. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2016.08.009" type="journal article" year="2017">
Nel 
<emphasis box="[1143,1192,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that acanthophorite spines (plesiomorphic) are present in the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nel, Garrouste &amp; Daugeron. Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[918,1029,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallica">
<emphasis box="[918,935,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[951,1029,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">gallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[1185,1320,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1320,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses some characters that are unique for microphorine genera: frons with three pairs of frontal-orbital setae (anterior pair inclinate) in both sexes; cell bm slender; cell cua slender and truncate apically. Some important characters remain unknown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[293,428,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,428,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; e.g., structure of the prothorax and antennal position. The costal vein ending at R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1359,1385,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">4+5</subScript>
was noted for both species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[431,566,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,566,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, this is not evident at least for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nel, Garrouste &amp; Daugeron. Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[1014,1122,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallica">
<emphasis box="[1014,1031,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1044,1122,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">gallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, A. &amp; Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C." box="[1136,1331,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref15625" refString="Nel, A., Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C. (2017) Two new long-legged flies in the Santonian amber of France (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Cretaceous Research, 69, 1 - 5. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2016.08.009" type="journal article" year="2017">
Nel 
<emphasis box="[1184,1233,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">et al</emphasis>
. 2017: 3
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2B). It is probably undisputable that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[507,642,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[507,642,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows closer affinities to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chvála" authorityYear="1981" box="[977,1157,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Parathalassiinae">Parathalassiinae</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[1188,1367,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dolichopodidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">
<taxonomicName box="[1374,1436,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">sensu</taxonomicName>
stricto
</emphasis>
lineage than to the 
<taxonomicName box="[442,562,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,562,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Microphor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genera group (
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[731,1047,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref14337" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (1999) Brachyceran Diptera in Cretaceous ambers and Mesozoic diversification of the Eremoneura. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 239, 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="1999">Grimaldi &amp; Cumming 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Brooks, S. E." box="[1059,1354,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref13849" refString="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Brooks, S. E. (2002) Electrophorella, a new genus of parathalassiine flies from Baltic amber, with a cladistic analysis of the Microphorinae + Dolichopodidae lineage (Diptera: Empidoidea). Studia dipterologica, 9 (1), 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2002">Cumming &amp; Brooks 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ulrich, H." pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="233 - 243" refId="ref16673" refString="Ulrich, H. (2004) Phylogenetic considerations about an early colonization of the sea coasts by Dolichopodidae (Diptera). Studia dipterologica, 11, 233 - 243." type="journal article" year="2004">Ulrich 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nel, A. &amp; Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C." box="[222,393,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref15625" refString="Nel, A., Garrouste, R. &amp; Daugeron, C. (2017) Two new long-legged flies in the Santonian amber of France (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Cretaceous Research, 69, 1 - 5. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2016.08.009" type="journal article" year="2017">
Nel 
<emphasis box="[269,319,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). See additional notes under 
<taxonomicName authority="Tang, Shi, Wang &amp; Yang." authorityName="Tang, Shi, Wang &amp; Yang." box="[715,1200,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Pristinmicrophor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,908,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Pristinmicrophor</emphasis>
Tang, Shi, Wang &amp; Yang.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
